{{title "Menu Sample | " @app.config.appName}}
{{#fillZone "content"}}
    <h3>Menu.</h3>
    <hr />
    <p>You can add a menu to your Application with following changes to the <code>config.yaml</code>.</p>
    <p>In your <code>config.yaml</code> file:</p>
    <pre>
        menu :
          main :
            Home : {link: "#", icon: "fw-home"}
            Pets :
              See all our amazing pets : {link: "pets"}
              Add a new pets : {link: "pets/new", icon: "fw fw-add"}
              Pet of the month : {link: "pets/snowball" }
    </pre>
    <p>
        Adding this will automatically picked up by <code>org.wso2.uuf.base.main</code> layout. However, if you are using
       your own layout,you can use "menu" helper.
    </p>
    <h3>Notes:</h3>
    <p>The default menu implementation will be supported only up to three levels.</p>
{{/fillZone}}